## 1️⃣ Payment Architecture

### 1.1 End-to-End Payment Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User (Browser)
    participant F as Frontend (Next.js)
    participant B as Backend API
    participant R as Razorpay
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    U->>F: Click "Upgrade to Pro"
    F->>B: POST /api/payment/create-order {planId}
    B->>B: Validate session, plan, eligibility
    B->>R: razorpay.orders.create()
    R-->>B: Order {id, amount, status}
    B->>DB: INSERT PaymentTransaction (status: "created")
    B-->>F: {orderId, amount, currency}
    F->>F: Load Razorpay Checkout SDK
    F->>R: Open Razorpay Checkout Modal
    U->>R: Enter payment details
    R-->>F: {razorpay_order_id, payment_id, signature}
    F->>B: POST /api/payment/verify {IDs + signature}
    B->>B: HMAC-SHA256 signature verification
    B->>R: Fetch payment details (double-check)
    B->>DB: UPDATE PaymentTransaction (status: "success")
    B->>DB: UPDATE User (plan, subscriptionStatus, dates)
    B->>U: 📧 Send confirmation email
    B-->>F: {success, subscription details}
    F->>U: 🎉 Show success, unlock features

    Note over R,B: Webhook (async backup)
    R->>B: POST /api/payment/webhook
    B->>B: Verify webhook signature
    B->>DB: Ensure user plan is updated
```

