## 2️⃣ User Account Flow

### 2.1 Authentication Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "Web Browser"
        WL["Login Page"] --> NA["NextAuth<br/>(Credentials + Google)"]
        NA --> JWT["JWT Cookie<br/>next-auth.session-token"]
    end

    subgraph "Android WebView"
        AL["Native Login"] --> NA2["POST /api/native-auth/email-login<br/>or /api/auth/webview-login"]
        NA2 --> PT["publicToken Cookie"]
    end

    subgraph "Backend"
        UNI["getUniversalSession()"] --> |"Check cookies"| DECIDE{Which cookie?}
        DECIDE --> |publicToken| PDB["Lookup by publicToken"]
        DECIDE --> |session-token| NAUTH["NextAuth getServerSession()"]
        PDB --> USER["User Object"]
        NAUTH --> USER
    end
```

### 2.2 Universal Session Handler

Your [getAndroidAuth.js](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/lib/getAndroidAuth.js) already implements a dual-auth strategy:

```javascript
// File: src/lib/getAndroidAuth.js

export async function getUniversalSession() {
    // 1. Android path: Check publicToken cookie
    const publicToken = cookieStore.get('publicToken')?.value;
    if (publicToken) {
        const user = await prisma.user.findFirst({
            where: { publicToken },
            select: { id, email, name, publicToken, onboarded }
        });
        if (user) return { user };
    }

    // 2. Web path: NextAuth session
    const session = await getServerSession(authOptions);
    return session;
}
```

### 2.3 User Data Model

```prisma
// File: prisma/schema.prisma — User model (lines 10-49)

model User {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  email       String   @unique
  password    String?                          // Hashed (credentials auth)
  publicToken String   @unique                 // Android auth token
  onboarded   Boolean  @default(false)

  // 💳 Subscription fields
  plan                 String   @default("free")   // "free" | "pro_monthly" | "pro_yearly" | "lifetime"
  paymentProvider      String?                      // "razorpay" | "stripe"
  subscriptionStatus   String?                      // "active" | "canceled" | "past_due"
  subscriptionStartDate DateTime?
  subscriptionEndDate   DateTime?
  trialEndDate          DateTime?

  // Relations
  paymentTransactions PaymentTransaction[]
  // ... habits, goals, reminders, settings, etc.
}
```

### 2.4 Premium Status Sync Across Devices

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Phone as 📱 Android App
    participant Web as 🌐 Website
    participant API as Backend
    participant DB as Database

    Note over Web: User upgrades on website
    Web->>API: POST /api/payment/verify
    API->>DB: UPDATE user SET plan='pro_monthly'
    API-->>Web: Premium unlocked ✅

    Note over Phone: Same user opens app
    Phone->>API: GET /api/payment/subscription
    API->>DB: SELECT plan, status FROM User
    DB-->>API: {plan: "pro_monthly", status: "active"}
    API-->>Phone: Premium status ✅

    Note over Phone: Features auto-unlock based on plan
```

**Key insight**: Premium status is stored in the [User](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/lib/subscription-middleware.js#9-35) table, not locally. Every API call from any device reads the same plan from the database. No local storage of premium status = no spoofing.

