## 6️⃣ Google Play Store Compliance

### 6.1 Policy Requirements & Your Compliance

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Google Play requires apps selling **digital goods** to use Google Play Billing. However, apps that **consume content generated outside the app** (e.g., website subscriptions) have more flexibility, as long as:
> - The app doesn't **prompt** for external payment inside the WebView
> - The user can use the app **without being forced to pay**
> - Premium is **account-based**, not device-based

### 6.2 Compliance Matrix

| Requirement | Your Implementation | Status |
|---|---|---|
| **No in-app payment prompts** | [shouldShowPaymentUI()](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/lib/platform-utils.js#65-81) returns `false` in WebView | ✅ |
| **App functional without payment** | Free tier: 3 habits, 3 goals, 7-day history | ✅ |
| **Account-based premium** | `User.plan` field in PostgreSQL, same across all devices | ✅ |
| **No pricing shown in app** | Platform messages: `"Additional services available on our website"` | ✅ |
| **External browser for payment** | `window.open(url, '_blank', 'noopener,noreferrer')` | ✅ |
| **Upgrade button opens browser** | "Continue on Website" → opens default browser | ✅ |
| **App description** | Must mention "subscription managed via website" | ⚠️ Verify |

