## 7️⃣ Security Best Practices

### 7.1 Security Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Request Security"
        RL["🚦 Rate Limiting<br/>10 orders/min/user"]
        CSP["🛡️ Content Security Policy<br/>Whitelisted domains only"]
        SEC_HEAD["📋 Security Headers<br/>X-Frame-Options<br/>X-Content-Type-Options<br/>X-XSS-Protection"]
    end
    
    subgraph "Auth Security"
        JWT_V["🔐 JWT Validation<br/>NEXTAUTH_SECRET"]
        PT_V["🎫 publicToken Validation<br/>DB lookup (Android)"]
        SESSION["🔑 Server-side sessions<br/>Never trust client"]
    end
    
    subgraph "Payment Security"
        SIG["✍️ HMAC-SHA256 Verification<br/>Razorpay signatures"]
        TIMING["⏱️ Timing-safe comparison<br/>crypto.timingSafeEqual()"]
        DOUBLE["🔍 Double verification<br/>Signature + API fetch"]
        IDEMP["🔄 Idempotency<br/>Prevent double processing"]
        WH_SIG["🔔 Webhook signature<br/>Separate webhook secret"]
    end
    
    subgraph "Data Security"
        PRISMA["📊 Prisma ORM<br/>SQL injection prevention"]
        ENV["🔒 Environment secrets<br/>Not in git, not in client"]
        NO_LEAK["🚫 No sensitive data<br/>in errors or logs"]
    end
```

### 7.2 Implemented Security Measures

| Security Measure | Implementation | File |
|---|---|---|
| **Signature verification** | HMAC-SHA256 + `timingSafeEqual` | [razorpay-provider.js](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/lib/payment/providers/razorpay-provider.js#L96-L139) |
| **Webhook verification** | Separate webhook secret + HMAC | [razorpay-provider.js](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/lib/payment/providers/razorpay-provider.js#L145-L174) |
| **Rate limiting** | 10 orders/min/user | [apiSecurity.js](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/lib/apiSecurity.js) |
| **CSP headers** | Razorpay/Stripe domains whitelisted | [middleware.js](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/middleware.js#L91-L93) |
| **Auth protection wrapper** | [withAPIProtection()](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/lib/apiSecurity.js#13-53) | [apiSecurity.js](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/lib/apiSecurity.js#L20-L52) |
| **Idempotency** | Check `transaction.status === 'success'` before processing | [verify/route.js](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/app/api/payment/verify/route.js) |
| **Input validation** | Prisma parameterized queries | All API routes |
| **Error sanitization** | No secrets in error responses | All API routes |

### 7.3 Preventing Payment Spoofing

```javascript
// ❌ NEVER trust client-side payment status
// The frontend cannot mark a user as premium

// ✅ ALWAYS verify server-side:
// Step 1: Verify Razorpay signature (HMAC-SHA256)
// Step 2: Fetch payment from Razorpay API (double-check)
// Step 3: Match order ID with database transaction
// Step 4: Only then update user.plan in database

// Webhook serves as async backup:
// Even if verify endpoint fails, webhook will catch it
```

### 7.4 CSP Policy (Already Configured)

```
Content-Security-Policy:
  default-src 'self';
  script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval' blob:
    https://checkout.razorpay.com
    https://js.stripe.com;
  connect-src 'self' https: https://checkout.razorpay.com;
  frame-src 'self' https://checkout.razorpay.com https://js.stripe.com;
```

