## 8️⃣ Performance Optimization

### 8.1 Current Optimizations

| Strategy | Implementation | Impact |
|---|---|---|
| **Lazy SDK loading** | Razorpay checkout.js loaded only on payment page | -150KB initial bundle |
| **Singleton provider** | [getProviderInstance()](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/lib/payment/payment-config.js#216-226) reuses Razorpay instance | Fewer API connections |
| **Lazy Razorpay import** | `await import('razorpay')` in provider | Faster cold start |
| **API response caching** | [api-cache.js](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/lib/api-cache.js) in-memory LRU | Fewer DB queries |
| **Database indexes** | On `providerOrderId`, `userId`, `status` | Fast payment lookups |
| **Prisma select optimization** | `select: { id, plan, ... }` only needed fields | Less data transfer |
| **Cache invalidation** | [cache-invalidation.js](file:///d:/startup/consistencygrid/src/lib/cache-invalidation.js) | Stale data prevention |

### 8.2 WebView Performance Tips

```javascript
// 1. Minimal API calls — batch where possible
// Example: /api/dashboard/stats returns everything in one call

// 2. Cache subscription status for 5 minutes
const SUBSCRIPTION_CACHE_TTL = 5 * 60 * 1000;

// 3. Lazy load heavy components
const PaymentCheckout = dynamic(() => 
    import('@/components/payment/PaymentCheckout'), 
    { ssr: false }
);

// 4. Service Worker for offline support (PWA)
// File: src/lib/pwa.js — already configured
```

### 8.3 Recommended Additional Optimizations

```javascript
// 1. Add subscription status to session token (avoid DB call per page)
// In authOptions callbacks:
callbacks: {
    async jwt({ token, user }) {
        if (user) {
            token.plan = user.plan;
            token.subscriptionStatus = user.subscriptionStatus;
        }
        return token;
    },
    async session({ session, token }) {
        session.user.plan = token.plan;
        session.user.subscriptionStatus = token.subscriptionStatus;
        return session;
    }
}

// 2. Prefetch subscription on app load
// In layout.js or dashboard:
useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/payment/subscription')
        .then(r => r.json())
        .then(data => setSubscription(data));
}, []);
```

